'''Gnome''' is a [[monster attribute]] in ''[[NetHack]]'' that indicates when a [[monster]] should be considered gnomish.{{refsrc|monflag.h|118|name=M2_GNOME|comment=monster attribute M2_GNOME}} It has many effects, but most significantly it helps determine whether your actions constitute [[cannibalism]] or same-race [[sacrifice]]. The gnome attribute is represented by the macro '''M2_GNOME'''.<ref name="M2_GNOME"/>

==Monsters==
In the [[dungeon]], you can encounter the following gnomish monsters:

* {{white|G}} {{monclasslink|G}}:
** {{monsymlink|gnome}}
** {{monsymlink|gnome lord}}
** {{monsymlink|gnome king}}
* [[undead]]
** {{monsymlink|gnome mummy}}
** {{monsymlink|gnome zombie}}

All gnomish monsters have "gnome" in their names.

==Description==
{{todo|this section is incomplete and requires expansion}}
The gnome attribute is used to determine the following things:

*If you are a [[Gnome (starting race)|gnomish player]], dwarf and gnome monsters are more likely to be [[peaceful]].{{refsrc|makemon.c|953|comment=possibly make monsters peaceful}}{{reffunc|makemon.c|peace_minded|comment=is monster peaceful?}}{{refsrc|mondata.h|102|comment=are these races peaceful?}}
*Whether [[eat]]ing a monster is [[cannibalism]] for a gnomish player.{{reffunc|eat.c|maybe_cannibal|comment=cannibalism}}{{refsrc|mondata.h|85|name=your_race|comment=compare races}}
*Whether a [[sacrifice]] is of your own race for an a dwarven player.<ref name="your_race"/>{{refsrc|pray.c|1167|comment=own-race sacrifice}}
*What to give when wishing for the [[corpse]]s of [[quest guardian]]s.{{refsrc|objnam.c|2560|comment=wishing for corpses}}{{reffunc|mon.c|genus|name=genus|comment=the race of a monster}}
*What responses to use when [[chat]]ting with other [[role]]s' quest guardians<ref name="genus"/>{{refsrc|sounds.c|439|comment=chatting to others' quest guardians}} (possibly created by [[reverse genocide]] or found in [[bones]]).

